# Plot every digit
def plot_d(digit, label):
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.imshow(digit.reshape((28,28)), cmap=plt.cm.gray)
    plt.title(label)
    
# Plot the digits on rows    
def plot_ds(digits, title, labels):
    n=digits.shape[0]
    n_rows=n/25+1
    n_cols=25
    plt.figure(figsize=(n_cols * 0.9, n_rows * 1.3))
    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0, hspace=0)
    plt.suptitle(title)
    for i in range(n):
        plt.subplot(n_rows, n_cols, i + 1)
        plot_d(digits[i,:], "%d" % labels[i])
        
# Having the predicted values, and the index of the cluster, plot it
def plot_cluster_2(predict, index):
    plot_ds(data[np.where(predict == index)],
            "Cluster: " + str(index) + " Purity: " + str(purity(labels,index)) + " Max elem: " + str(np.argmax(np.bincount(labels[np.where(predict == index)]))),
            (labels[np.where(predict == index)]))
    
#Divide the number of occurrences of the most repeated number among the total
def purity(labels, n):
    unique, counts = np.unique(labels[np.where(predict == n)], return_counts=True)
    purityPercent = np.divide(float(np.amax(counts)),labels[np.where(predict == n)].size)
    return round(purityPercent,4)

# Print the stats of a given stimator
def printStats(estimator, data, name):
    print(82 * '_')
    t0=time()
    if(name=='random' or name == 'k-means++' or name=='pca'):
        print('init\t\ttime\tinertia\thomo\tcompl\tv-meas\tARI\tAMI\tsilhouette')
        estimator.fit(data)
        print('%-9s\t%.2fs\t%i\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f'
              % (name, (time() - t0), estimator.inertia_,
                 metrics.homogeneity_score(labels, estimator.labels_),
                 metrics.completeness_score(labels, estimator.labels_),
                 metrics.v_measure_score(labels, estimator.labels_),
                 metrics.adjusted_rand_score(labels, estimator.labels_),
                 metrics.adjusted_mutual_info_score(labels,  estimator.labels_),
                 metrics.silhouette_score(data, estimator.labels_,
                                          metric='euclidean',
                                          sample_size=1000)))
    else:
        print('init\t\ttime\t\thomo\tcompl\tv-meas\tARI\tAMI\tsilhouette')
        estimator.fit(data)
        labels_est = estimator.predict(data)
        print('%-9s\t%.2fs\t\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f\t%.3f'
          % (name, (time() - t0),
             metrics.homogeneity_score(labels, labels_est ),
             metrics.completeness_score(labels, labels_est ),
             metrics.v_measure_score(labels, labels_est ),
             metrics.adjusted_rand_score(labels, labels_est ),
             metrics.adjusted_mutual_info_score(labels, labels_est, average_method='arithmetic' ),
             metrics.silhouette_score(data, labels_est ,
                                      metric='euclidean',
                                      sample_size=1000)))
        
# Part of the code of this fuction has been taken from sklearn documentation page.
# Given an estimator, plot the points and and color the corresponding area to each cluster.
def getGraph(estimator,name):
    reduced_data = PCA(n_components=2).fit_transform(data)
    estimator.fit(reduced_data)

    # Step size of the mesh. Decrease to increase the quality of the VQ.
    h = .02     # point in the mesh [x_min, x_max]x[y_min, y_max].

    # Plot the decision boundary. For that, we will assign a color to each
    x_min, x_max = reduced_data[:, 0].min() - 1, reduced_data[:, 0].max() + 1
    y_min, y_max = reduced_data[:, 1].min() - 1, reduced_data[:, 1].max() + 1
    xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, h), np.arange(y_min, y_max, h))

    # Obtain labels for each point in mesh. Use last trained model.
    Z = estimator.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])

    # Put the result into a color plot
    Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)
    plt.figure(1)
    plt.clf()
    t = plt.imshow(Z, interpolation='nearest',
               extent=(xx.min(), xx.max(), yy.min(), yy.max()),
               cmap=plt.cm.Paired,
               aspect='auto', origin='lower')

    plt.plot(reduced_data[:, 0], reduced_data[:, 1], 'k.', markersize=2)
  
    # Plot the centroids as a white X
    if(name == 'kmeans'):
        centroids = estimator.cluster_centers_
        plt.scatter(centroids[:, 0], centroids[:, 1],
                    marker='x', s=169, linewidths=3,
                    color='w', zorder=10)
    plt.title( name + ' clustering on the digits dataset (PCA-reduced data)\n'
              'Centroids are marked with white cross')
    plt.xlim(x_min, x_max)
    plt.ylim(y_min, y_max)
    plt.xticks(())
    plt.yticks(())
    plt.colorbar(t)
    plt.show()
    
# Given an estimator, plot the points on a graph  
def printOnGraph(data, estimator, name):
    
    if(name=='original'):
        # Reduce the dimensions of the data using PCA
        reduced_data = PCA(n_components=2).fit_transform(data)

        plt.scatter(reduced_data[:, 0], reduced_data[:, 1], c=labels[:], edgecolor='none',
                   cmap=plt.get_cmap('jet', 10), s=10)
        plt.title('Original data', fontdict=None, loc='center')
        plt.colorbar()   
   
    else:
        reduced_data = PCA(n_components=2).fit_transform(data)
        estimator.fit(reduced_data)
        pred = estimator.predict(reduced_data)
        # Plot two grapths simultaneusly
        f, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, sharey=True)
        sc = ax1.scatter(reduced_data[:, 0], reduced_data[:, 1], c=pred[:], edgecolor='none',
               cmap=plt.get_cmap('jet', 10), s=10)
        ax1.set_title(name)


        ax2.scatter(reduced_data[:, 0], reduced_data[:, 1], c=labels[:], edgecolor='none',
               cmap=plt.get_cmap('jet', 10), s=10)
        ax2.set_title('Original data')

        plt.colorbar(sc)
        # Change the size of the graphs
        plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = [8,5]
        plt.show()
